Title: Unspoken Truths
Credit: Written by ChatGPT
Date: August 6, 2025

INT. COFFEE SHOP - LATE AFTERNOON

A warm, cozy coffee shop tucked away from the busy street. The rain taps gently on the window. SARAH (28), witty and observant, sits across from MIKE (30), calm and analytical. JENNY (26), energetic and always smiling, joins them with three drinks in hand.

                    JENNY
    Triple espresso for the brooding philosopher,
    oat latte for the realist, and chai for me!

                    MIKE
    (smirks)
    I’m not brooding. I’m contemplating.

                    SARAH
    That’s just a fancy word for spiraling.

They laugh. Jenny sits down, sliding the drinks across the table.

                    JENNY
    So... are we ever going to talk about it?

                    SARAH
    Talk about what?

                    JENNY
    You and Mike. The tension is thicker than this foam.

Awkward silence. Mike takes a slow sip of his drink.

                    MIKE
    It's not tension. It’s just... history.

                    SARAH
    (softly)
    History doesn’t mean it’s finished.

Jenny looks between them, surprised.

                    JENNY
    Wait—was this a thing?

                    MIKE
    Past tense, Jenny.

                    SARAH
    Maybe. But past doesn’t mean irrelevant.

Beat. The rain grows louder outside. Jenny fidgets with her cup.

                    JENNY
    Well, this just got dramatic.

                    MIKE
    Welcome to Wednesday.

                    SARAH
    (smiling)
    It’s good to say it out loud though.

                    JENNY
    You two really need to go on a hike or scream into a void or something.

                    MIKE
    This coffee shop *is* my void.

They laugh again. The tension dissolves just a little.

FADE OUT.

